Cards.title: • Nexus Account / Token Generator
Cards.description: High-quality Discord account and token generator with browser-based HCaptcha solving, account verification via mail API, and built-in account humanization — completely free and open source.
Cards.full_description: The Nexus Account / Token Generator is a powerful, free and open-source tool developed in collaboration between Rickware - Labs and Nexus. It generates high-quality, fully unlocked Discord tokens using a sophisticated pipeline that includes browser-based HCaptcha solving via a custom HTML file, Discord account verification through a dedicated mail API, and a humanization layer that makes generated accounts behave like real users to avoid detection. Built with Python and JavaScript, the tool is actively maintained and supports proxy usage — NullProxies is the recommended provider for the most seamless experience. The generator is completely free and available directly on GitHub.

Cards.title: • Nexus Account / Token Server Joiner
Cards.description: Automated Discord server joiner that mass-joins servers using token lists with proxy support, rate limit handling, and built-in error recovery — free and open source.
Cards.full_description: The Nexus Account / Token Server Joiner is a free, open-source automation tool developed in collaboration between Rickware - Labs and Nexus. It allows you to mass-join Discord servers using lists of user tokens, with full proxy support to distribute requests and avoid rate limiting. The tool handles errors gracefully, retries failed joins automatically, and provides detailed output logs for every operation. Whether you need to populate a server quickly or manage multiple account joins in bulk, this tool streamlines the entire process with minimal configuration. Built with Python, it is lightweight, fast, and easy to run on any system. Available directly on GitHub at no cost.

Cards.title: • Account / Token Checker - (Verified)
Cards.description: Fast and reliable Discord token checker that validates account status, flags locked or disabled tokens, and exports clean results — completely free and verified.
Cards.full_description: The Account / Token Checker is a fast, free, and open-source utility for validating Discord tokens in bulk. Simply paste or import a list of tokens and the tool will check each one against Discord's API, identifying which accounts are valid and active, which are locked, phone-verified, or email-verified, and which have been disabled or banned. Results are sorted and exportable, making it easy to filter your token pool for high-quality accounts. The tool runs with minimal dependencies, supports proxy input to avoid rate limiting on large batches, and provides a clean visual summary of results. Verified and trusted by the community, with the full source code available on GitHub.

Cards.title: • Bot Client - (Vencord Built-In)
Cards.description: Use a Discord bot token like a normal user account — a fully functional Discord client built for bot tokens with Vencord already integrated out of the box.
Cards.full_description: The Bot Client with built-in Vencord allows you to run a Discord bot token as if it were a regular user account inside a fully featured Discord client. This open-source project, originally developed by aiko-chan-ai, provides a complete browser-based Discord experience for bot tokens — including message reading, server navigation, and channel interaction — without the usual restrictions that come with bot-only API access. Vencord is pre-integrated, giving you access to a wide range of client-side plugins, themes, and quality-of-life improvements right out of the box. Ideal for developers, selfbot experimenters, and advanced Discord users who need a clean and functional interface for their bot accounts.

Cards.title: • Requestcord API Wrapper - (For Developer)
Cards.description: Advanced Discord API wrapper with modern features
Cards.full_description: A modern, lightweight Discord API wrapper for Python focused on speed, simplicity, and clean request handling. RequestCord is built for developers who want direct access to Discord's REST API without heavy abstractions or browser automation.
